OL,7,FWhen asked about the latest criticism,
OL,8,FDeputy Prime Minister Angela Rayner
OL,9,Fsaid: "It's not softening crime, it's
OL,10,Fabout making sure we build the prisons
OL,11,Fwe need, we've got the bobbies on the
OL,12,Fbeat, and we're making sure that
OL,13,Fpeople are safe in their communities."
OL,15,FConservative shadow minister, Helen
OL,16,FWhately, said Labour "needs to sort
OL,17,Fthis out" and "take responsibility"
OL,18,Ffor ensuring there were enough prison
OL,19,Fplaces, adding: "They are the guys who
OL,20,Fare in government now."
